 174:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c **** /**
 175:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   * @brief  isp_ae_get_new_exposure
 176:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         This function computes the new sensor exposure to be applied
 177:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         for a given lux and a given luminance target
 178:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         This function is implemented in accordance with the exposure estimation
 179:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         principles based on the estimated lux value of the current scene.
 180:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         There are 3 models of new sensor exposure estimation used in this AE algorithm:
 181:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         - Estimation 1 is used for values above ­ØÉ┐­Øæó­Øæź­Øæģ­ØæÆ­Øæō_­ØÉ╗­ØÉ┐
 182:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         - Estimation 2 is used for values below ­ØÉ┐­Øæó­Øæź­Øæģ­ØæÆ­Øæō_­ØÉ╗­ØÉ┐ and above ­Øæ
 183:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         - Estimation 3 is used for values from 0 to ­ØæÉ­Øæó­ØæĀ­ØæĪ­Øæ£­ØæÜ_­ØæÖ­Øæ£­Øæż_­ØæÖ­
 184:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *           ­ØæÉ­Øæó­ØæĀ­ØæĪ­Øæ£­ØæÜ_­ØæÖ­Øæ£­Øæż_­ØæÖ­Øæó­Øæź_­ØæÖ­Øæ¢­ØæÜ­Øæ¢­ØæĪ should be set
 185:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *           ­ØæÄ_­ØÉ┐­ØÉ┐├Ś­ØæÖ­Øæó­ØæÜ_­ØæĪ­ØæÄ­Øæ¤­Øæö­ØæÆ­ØæĪ├Ś­ØæÉ­ØæÄ­ØæÖ­Øæ¢­ØæÅ­ØÉ╣­ØæÄ­Øæ
 186:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         Two types of convergence are targeted:
 187:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         - COARSE CONVERGENCE: in the 1st iteration, the exposure calculation brings
 188:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *           the luminance value close to the target
 189:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *         - FINE CONVERGENCE: in the following iteration,  if fine convergence has not been
 190:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *           achieved yet with the previous calculation, small increments are applied to
 191:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   *           reach high accuracy.
 192:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   * @param  lux      : current lux value of the captured scene
 193:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   * @param  averageL : current average luminance statistic
 194:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   * @param  pExposure: pointer to the new exposure time value (us)
 195:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   * @param  pGain    : pointer to the new sensor gain value (mdB)
 196:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   * @param  exposure : current sensor exposure time value (us)
 197:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   * @param  gain     : current sensor gain value (mdB)
 198:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   * @retval None
 199:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c ****   */
 200:../Middlewares/stm32-mw-camera/ISP_Library/isp/Src/isp_ae_algo.c **** void isp_ae_get_new_exposure(uint32_t lux, uint32_t averageL, uint32_t *pExposure, uint32_t *pGain,
